Correlation

Calculate the three correlation coefficients between Household Income, House Value, and percent 18-21. Use these correlation coefficients in a sentence without typing the numbers in directly. (i.e. your markdown file should generate the coefficient automatically for you).

The correlation coefficient between Household Income (MEDHHINC) and House Value (MEDHVALUE) is 0.84. The correlation coefficient between Household Income (MEDHHINC) and the percentage of the population aged 18-21 (college_frac) is -0.31. Lastly, the correlation coefficient between House Value (MEDHVALUE) and the percentage of the population aged 18-21 (college_frac) is -0.2.
